trend_summary: Imagery reveals steady 20-year suburbanisation: new north–south highway, spreading housing tracts and commercial nodes replace farmland, while maturing tree cover softens the landscape. Built area grows but large forest patches remain, keeping overall medium-density, car-oriented suburbia.
notable_changes: New north–south arterial highway with multiple interchanges constructed mid-period.
Residential subdivisions expand outward, especially in central and southern zones.
Commercial/industrial park added near the southern boundary along major roads.
Agricultural fields in the north converted to mixed woodland and recreation areas.
Tree canopy density increases in older neighborhoods, indicating landscape maturation.
